<li><a href="/wiki/Richard_I._Cohen" title="Richard I. Cohen">Richard I. Cohen</a>: winner of the Arnold Wischnitzer Prize (1998)<sup id="cite_ref-17" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-17">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Natalie_Zemon_Davis" title="Natalie Zemon Davis">Natalie Zemon Davis</a>: winner of the <a href="/wiki/Holberg_Prize" title="Holberg Prize">Holberg International Memorial Prize</a> (2010); Companion of the <a href="/wiki/Order_of_Canada" title="Order of Canada">Order of Canada</a>; recipient of the <a href="/wiki/National_Humanities_Medal" title="National Humanities Medal">National Humanities Medal</a> (2012).<sup id="cite_ref-18" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-18">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></li>
